JOHANNESBURG - One of South Africa's most famous poets has delivered a tribute to Mama Winnie. Lebo Mashile recited a piece by the writer Alice Walker. "The Color Purple" author wrote the moving tribute to Madikizela-Mandela in the 1980s READ: US novelist Alice Walker's tribute to Madikizela-Mandela The poem was published while former president Nelson Mandela was still imprisoned on Robben Island. It was a tribute to her strength, which led to her recognition by the oppressed as the "Mother of the Nation". Madikizela-Mandela was arguably the most prominent female face of the liberation movement in South Africa. You can listen to Mashile's reading of the poem in the video box above. eNCA